description.narrative:
The high-level multi-stakeholder platform on the implementation of the Sustainable Development Goals was established to:

- act as a convener, facilitator, catalyst, broker and activator helping all interested actors to meet and exchange information, ideas and experiences and turn expertise and knowledge into practice; 
- be a collector and transmitter of best practices, both by countries and within organizations. 
- pro-actively communicate to key stakeholders in and outside of Geneva, including governments, United Nations system and other international organizations, the private sector, civil society organizations and academic institutions, etc., the latest collective developments on the SDGs; 
	- develop a multi-faceted network with all relevant stakeholders to strengthen the SDG implementation community, ensure common objectives and shared incentives to actively implement the SDGs; 
- identify strategic opportunities for multi-stakeholder convergence in order to energize and maximize the added-value of International Geneva in supporting the implementation of the SDGs; 
- generate and catalyze momentum on follow-up action to the commitments on the SDGs; 
- create space and actively convene stakeholders to foster an inter-sectoral exchange leading to concrete initiatives and partnerships to support the implementation Of the SDGs; 
- enhance international support for implementing effective and targeted capacity-building in developing countries to contribute to national plans to implement the SDGs, including through North-South, South-South and triangular cooperation; 
- work in close partnership with UN entities and other stakeholders in and outside Geneva, in ensuring strong and consistent sharing of information and integration of action across the United Nations system and its partners. 

UNOPS supports the human resource and administrative management for the Senior 
Manager in charge of the coordination of the SDG Multi Stakeholder Platform. Staff and 
related office cost (including office rental and equipment, travel, IT support and other non- 
staff costs) are funded by the Swiss Confederation.
